  "chapter": {
    "bookTitle": "D&C",
    "delineation": "Section",
    "number": 83,
    "summary": "1–4, Women and children have claim upon their husbands and fathers for their support; 5–6, Widows and orphans have claim upon the Church for their support.",
    "chapterAugmentations": [],
    "verses": [
      {
        "text": "Verily, thus saith the Lord, in addition to the laws of the church concerning women and children, those who belong to the church, who have lost their husbands or fathers:",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "D&C 51:8 (7–14).",
            "start": 48,
            "end": 52
          },
          {
            "footnote": "Deut. 10:18; Isa. 1:17 (16–17); James 1:27.",
            "start": 139,
            "end": 143
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Women have claim on their husbands for their maintenance, until their husbands are taken; and if they are not found transgressors they shall have fellowship in the church.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "D&C 75:25.",
            "start": 0,
            "end": 5
          },
          {
            "footnote": "1 Tim. 5:8 (8–16).",
            "start": 11,
            "end": 16
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Family, Patriarchal; Marriage, Husbands.",
            "start": 70,
            "end": 78
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "And if they are not faithful they shall not have fellowship in the church; yet they may remain upon their inheritances according to the laws of the land.",
        "footnotes": [],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "All children have claim upon their parents for their maintenance until they are of age.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "Mosiah 4:14 (14–15). TG Children.",
            "start": 4,
            "end": 12
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Birth Control.",
            "start": 35,
            "end": 42
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Family, Children, Responsibilities toward.",
            "start": 53,
            "end": 64
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "And after that, they have claim upon the church, or in other words upon the Lord's storehouse, if their parents have not wherewith to give them inheritances.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "D&C 51:4 (3–4).",
            "start": 26,
            "end": 31
          },
          {
            "footnote": "D&C 78:3. TG Welfare.",
            "start": 83,
            "end": 93
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "And the storehouse shall be kept by the consecrations of the church; and widows and orphans shall be provided for, as also the poor. Amen.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "Deut. 14:29; Mal. 3:5; Acts 4:35. TG Widows.",
            "start": 73,
            "end": 79
          },
          {
            "footnote": "Zech. 7:10; Mosiah 4:26 (16–26); Hel. 4:12; D&C 42:30 (30–39, 71).",
            "start": 127,
            "end": 131
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      }
    ]
  }
